text: Fuad II (, full name: Ahmed Fuad bin Farouk bin Ahmed Fuad bin Ismail bin Ibrahim bin Muhammad Ali; born 16 January 1952) or alternatively Ahmed Fuad II is a member of the Egyptian Muhammed Ali Dynasty. He was the King of Egypt and the Sudan from 1952 until the monarchy was abolished in 1953. Since then, Fuad was the claimant to the Egyptian throne and is the Head of the Royal House of Egypt since his father's death in 1965. == Related pages == *Lists of state leaders by age Category:1952 births Category:House of Alawiyya Category:Kings and Queens of Egypt Category:20th century in Egypt Category:21st century in Egypt
